            <listEvent>
                <event type="researchStep">
                    <head type="stepTitle" xml:lang="en">Associate keywords to the scenario or the
                        step</head>
                    <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en">The SSK vocabularies are:<list>
                            <item><ref type="specification"
                                    target="https://ssk-application.parthenos.d4science.org/ssk/#/glossary/activities"
                                    >Research activities</ref>, taken from <ref type="specification"
                                    target="https://github.com/dhtaxonomy/TaDiRAH"
                                >Tadirah</ref>.</item>
                            <item><ref type="specification"
                                    target="https://ssk-application.parthenos.d4science.org/ssk/#/glossary/techniques"
                                    >Research techniques</ref>, taken from <ref type="specification"
                                    target="https://github.com/dhtaxonomy/TaDiRAH"
                                >Tadirah</ref>.</item>
                            <item><ref type="specification"
                                    target="https://ssk-application.parthenos.d4science.org/ssk/#/glossary/objects"
                                    >Research objects</ref>, taken from <ref type="specification"
                                    target="https://github.com/dhtaxonomy/TaDiRAH">Tadirah</ref> and
                                    <ref type="specification"
                                    target="http://nemo.dcu.gr/index.php?p=navigate#"
                                >NeDiMAH</ref></item>
                            <item><ref type="documentation"
                                    target="https://ssk-application.parthenos.d4science.org/ssk/#/glossary/standards"
                                    >Standards</ref>, taken from the SSK Standard Knowledge base
                                (supported by DARIAH-IT)</item>
                            <item><ref type="documentation"
                                    target="https://ssk-application.parthenos.d4science.org/ssk/#/glossary/disciplines"
                                    >Disciplines</ref>, taken from <ref type="specification"
                                    target="https://aurehal.archives-ouvertes.fr/domain?locale=en"
                                    >aureHAL</ref></item>
                        </list>When editing the description of a scenario, the available keywords
                        are: <list>
                            <item>Disciplines</item>
                            <item>Techniques</item>
                            <item>Objects</item>
                            <item>Standards</item>
                        </list>For the steps, the most important keyword is the Activity, that
                        should be unique for each step. It also possible to pick some techniques,
                        objects and standards. In general, for each keyword type, we recommend to choosse between 1 and 4 keywords.</desc>
                    <desc xml:lang="en" type="terms">
                        <term type="activity" source="http://tadirah.dariah.eu/" key="annotating"
                            >annotating</term>
                    </desc>
                    <linkGrp type="generalResources">
                        <ref type="documentation"/>
                    </linkGrp>
                </event>
